JOHN: Uh, the rearview mirror.

20:34.500 --> 20:36.934
Uh, "Objects in mirror may be
closer than they appear."

20:37.000 --> 20:38.300
Right!

20:38.367 --> 20:40.333
JOHN: <i>It seemed like I had found</i>
<i>the one place</i>

20:40.400 --> 20:44.834
<i>where the worse your memory was,</i>
<i>the more people liked you.</i>

20:44.900 --> 20:46.433
<i>And they would go</i>
<i>to great lengths</i>

20:46.500 --> 20:48.700
<i>to make you feel accepted.</i>

20:48.767 --> 20:49.800
JERRY: Here we go!

20:51.033 --> 20:53.633
"Objects in mirror are closer
than they appear."

20:53.700 --> 20:55.467
JOHN: 'Cause you remember
"may be," right?

20:55.533 --> 20:56.633
JERRY: Yes, sir!

20:56.700 --> 20:58.700
(BOTH LAUGHING)

20:58.767 --> 21:02.033
JOHN: <i>It felt kind of nice</i>
<i>to be validated so easily.</i>

21:02.100 --> 21:05.100
<i>And I was almost sad that</i>
<i>it was time to go back home.</i>

21:06.367 --> 21:08.500
<i>When I landed in New York,</i>
<i>I was hungry,</i>

21:08.567 --> 21:09.867
<i>so I stopped for lunch</i>

21:09.934 --> 21:14.233
<i>at an airport restaurant</i>
<i>called CBGB.</i>

21:14.300 --> 21:17.300
<i>It seemed like it had a lot</i>
<i>of music-themed decor,</i>

21:17.367 --> 21:19.934
<i>but I was here for the food.</i>

21:20.000 --> 21:22.333
<i>I ended up getting their, uh,</i>
<i>signature hot dog</i>

21:22.400 --> 21:23.533
<i>for twelve dollars,</i>

21:24.300 --> 21:26.100
<i>and it wasn't half bad.</i>

21:29.266 --> 21:31.533
<i>When I got home,</i>
<i>I tried to write everything</i>

21:31.600 --> 21:33.967
<i>from that weekend</i>
<i>down in my calendar,</i>

21:34.033 --> 21:37.767
<i>but I got distracted and started</i>
<i>looking at old entries.</i>

21:37.834 --> 21:40.166
<i>And I eventually</i>
<i>read everything, uh,</i>

21:40.233 --> 21:42.200
<i>from the beginning,</i>
<i>chronologically.</i>

21:43.433 --> 21:45.266
<i>It was the first time</i>
<i>I had ever done that,</i>

21:45.333 --> 21:48.100
<i>and it felt like I was reading</i>
<i>about a different person.</i>

21:49.300 --> 21:52.467
<i>I remember being spontaneous</i>
<i>in my 20s,</i>

21:52.533 --> 21:56.700
<i>but everything I read proved</i>
<i>that I was a slave to routine.</i>

21:56.767 --> 21:59.433
<i>And I noticed</i>
<i>relationship patterns</i>

21:59.500 --> 22:01.433
<i>that I had been</i>
<i>trying to ignore.</i>

22:03.133 --> 22:05.467
<i>By the end of it,</i>
<i>I was in a terrible mood.</i>

22:05.533 --> 22:07.934
<i>And I realized</i>
<i>that maybe it's unnatural</i>

22:08.000 --> 22:10.400
<i>to try to preserve some things.</i>

22:13.800 --> 22:15.967
<i>The way the past exists</i>
<i>in our head</i>

22:16.033 --> 22:18.934
<i>is not always the way</i>
<i>that we experienced it.</i>

22:19.000 --> 22:20.567
<i>And at the end of the day,</i>

22:20.633 --> 22:22.400
<i>there will always be distortions</i>

22:22.467 --> 22:24.233
<i>as long as humans</i>
<i>are responsible</i>

22:24.300 --> 22:25.934
<i>for remembering everything.</i>

22:26.900 --> 22:30.367
<i>So enjoy this fantasy</i>
<i>while you can,</i>

22:30.433 --> 22:32.834
<i>because if you're having</i>
<i>a bad day today,</i>

